content:
Made bacon my favorite way in the oven this morning after work.
Cold oven. 
400 degrees.  Do not wait to warm it up.  Bacon goes right in.  
(Aluminum foil on baking sheet under bacon to ease in clean up.)
Bake bacon for 24 minutes, keep oven closed.
Peek in after 20 minutes -- make sure it is looking the way you like.
Drain over cooling rack and paper towels.  Get ready for BLTs for supper baby!
